deck: The estranged granddaughter of notorious superpowered gangster; Charlie Arrows. A real chip off his old block who works as an enforcer to Dr. Orwell.
description:
A hardened street tough killer in service to the ruthless time traveler named Orwell, the Granddaughter of Charlie Arrows and his late fling; Rose Ann Marsh. She was born as her mother passed away during childbirth and came into the care of her only remaining relative but quickly absconded the scene of her cloistered childhood and overbearing surrogate parent.

Growing up orphaned and alone she eventually came into her own abnormal abilities inherited from her paternal forefather whom she never knew. Using these odd talents of superspeed coupling in a razor aura which could cut through anything or anyone she ran through, Lucy managed to survive the streets for a time taking whatever she needed to in order to get by.

Eventually she'd come into the service of an ingenious yet morally ambiguous Professor who runs a tight clandestine outfit backed by several highly influential individuals within seats particularly influential in corporate welfare. This man named Orwell would offer her a job as personal bodyguard and enforcer, while at the same time teach her in the usage of her powers making her a more effective agent.
name: Lucy Arrows

description:
History

Monan was one of Randac's chief scientists during his reign and knew of the formula to create terrigen crystals. Monan is a distant relative of Lineage; this meant while Lineage was alive he was trapped within Lineage's body for the Inhuman to be available whenever he required information.

Inhumans vs. X-Men

Maximus ordered Lineage to use his ability to pull Monan out so that he could speak with him. Lineage obliged, and Maximus acquired Monan's information regarding the formula to craft terrigen crystals. Once said information was relayed Maximus stabbed the manifestation of Monan with a fork freeing him from Lineage's grasp ensuring that he was the only one with the information and the only one who could stop the Inhuman and Mutant conflict.
name: Monan

deck: Marvel Golden Age character who was possessed by a demon and operated as member of the Crazy S.U.E.S. during WWII.
description:
Preface

Davey Drew was one of many costumed operatives active during World War II who were recruited into the United States military under Operation: Firefly. The purpose of their enlistment was for the United States military to distribute propaganda in the form of comic books that were published by Timely Comics. These comics were used to convince Americans to support the war, and increase enlistment.

Crazy S.U.E.S.

Not much is known about the true origin Davey Drew, it seems as though Davey was possessed by or had merged with a Demon, as the creature's ethereal form surrounded over Davey's own body at all times.

When the Untied States entered into World War II, Davey was drafted into the military and was assigned to the Specialized Unit, Enhanced Soldiers (or the Crazy Sues) under the command of Captain America. In August of 1942, Davey and his comrades were deployed to Guadalcanal where they battled the Imperial Japanese Army.

During one such clash with Japanese forces, the Crazy SUES were forced to pull back while their teammate, Captain Flame, used his fire-based powers on the opposing forces. Both Davey and Jap Buster Johnson refused orders to pull back. Captain Flame's powers incinerated Johnson and horribly burned Davey's face, severely effecting his mental state. Davey continued to fight alongside the Crazy Sues until they were redeployed to Europe in 1944, where they participated in the Battle of Normandy. Following the battle, Davey and his comrades celebrated their victory with the Invaders.

Davey has not been seen since, his subsequent fate is unknown.
